task.summary: Default task
Fixed bug where svn error would not show on admin page
Added basic admin deletion of repo functionality
Added favicon. Fixed wording of project selection when no projects exist.

Fixed a bug when creating a project and inserting duplicate metadata key when creating project from template.
Added more checks to abort during the end of the local setup process
Added basic stats page for administrator panel
Added warning to revision counter when selecting a revision prior to the earliest for a specific file.
After selecting first DIFF item, the last revision and the same tree item are automatically selected.
Editor top commit box for SVNCLIENT is only shown after edits are made which scroll the page beyond the top of the panel.
Modified title and appearance of new folder/file buttons

Fixed bugs:
-Incorrect numbers displayed for writable and accessable projects -New folder and New file buttons active when location read-only -download feature not working due to audit variable typo
Fixed a bug where the userid would not show up on the password reset box

Changed 'metadata editor' to capitol 'E' in administrative view Added first version of analysis script wrappers, with install and uninstall scripts. As discussed, the scripts overlap the original scripts for nmfe and PsN.

Fixed a bug where the path would get truncated because non-alphanumeric chars were entered. Other characters are okay for paths in general, but we will have to look specifics ones like backslash and dot when creating a new file or folder. Fixed a bug where file uploaded would not work more than once with the same file chosen.
Fixed an issue where users permissions were not removed from the root of the project Fixed an issue where search results would appear from projects which users did not have access to.
Monkey-patched a problem with uploading a file with spaces in the name by manually uri encoding it in.

Added functions file in auxutils to hold basic functions which do not have to do with connections. Added ASCII truncate function to aforementioned file fixed writing output file by .encoding to utf-8 on setContents method (from built-in editor)

Added functions file in auxutils to hold basic functions which do not have to do with connections. Added ASCII truncate function to aforementioned file fixed writing output file by .encoding to utf-8 on setContents method (from built-in editor) Added check to new file/folder dialogs to disallow slashes.
Added a bunch more audit actions

Added basic viewing and deleting of error messages but to cluster rollbacks
fixed exception styles for aws cloudformation somewhat to make the error look more professional put a max hardcoded limit on node cluster size in checker.
Removed brute-force method from AWS stack modification commands

fixed editing metadata to not use /admin path for select field fixed editMeta path to work for select fields added new audit type 'createmeta' which only fires for creating metadata, while editmeta is not for editing only
Fixed all svn routes which were set to require login level (4) to level (2) instead.
Fixed an issue where jquery UI would not show up correctly
Initial change to fix an issue where added/removed nodes would not allow the keyfile to be downloaded.
Decreased the sshServerAlive interval value to 15 seconds. Added a basic emergency cluster unmount feature.
Fixed issue in removeall mountings with the wrong user hardcoded in the string.

enabled lock deletion on checker
Fixed issue with javascript being deleted for error dismissing functions
Fixed auditing of deletion of metadata, which was not working previously.

Added a new feature to prepare incase some emergency happens with one of our features, which would render SVN not usable correctly. (Unlikely but I like to prepare for the worst) The new features automatically prepares users which just have been given access to a repository automatic authentication with rabbitVCS, so that both Sonic and Rabbit can be used together Easily. This is not really limited to rabbit either, as it uses SVN global credential storage - and linux SVN client should work, but I have only tested with rabbit.
Fixed a bug in internet explorer making the height of the graphs incorrect.
Finished some bugfixes for the remote cluster auditing, the first version works well now.

Added AWS_ENABLE config option. If this is false, all aws related features are disabled. On the server side, this involved one extra decorator for JSON api queries and also one classic IF/THEN construction for the createnewcluster function (which does not use the JSON api). Client side one extra javascript page variable was added and checked which disables various related buttons.

Added a cluster type 'local cluster'. Added two dummy routes to help set up the data template in mongodb, but they can be modified by the administrator after. These clusters appear for all users and may not be modified or turned on and off in any way. The purpose is just to get a view of the cpu usage and such. The checker process for getting the cpu usage for these clusters is not actually developed yet, but it is the next priority.
Modified checker.py algorithm to work with local clusters type. Only cpu and ram will be updated.

Updated modal display in svn client and admin. new function 'dispModal' takes care of determining the error or message and showing the correct modal. Also updated the formatting of the modal.
When choosing to 'update' from SVN, conflict files are checked for, and a message is displayed informing the users that they should check and resolve the conflict.

Fixed a bug where loading spinnear would appear before selecting a project on the svn admin menu.
Fixed a bug where the flashed messages would still show errors when AWS was turned off.

Fixed a bug where svn search would not work due to past changes regarding user access fixes. I am not sure who came up with the solution (me), but for both the project search as well as the global seaerch the sarch was depending on metadata which did not exist. (For global, the 'users' was not present in all metadata), (For project, the 'proj' field was not always present) Anyway, we now get all results fom DB and filter based on user access. If this proves too slow in the future we can add the required fields for filtering and return to the other strategy.

'Official' sonic 2.0 release, for some reason.
Fixed error messages for SVN connections. Every call to svn connection is wrapped now.

changed 'app' to appc' in most places in order to avoid name conflict with app package.
created basic cache code using memcached. project creation is modified to implement a post commit hook for updating the cache.
reverted appc to app because it did not fix the issue.
Added manual cache-free refresh button, which allows the user to get the latest copy manually.

Fixed a bug with small repositories where celery would not lock the svn project for the get_sync method in time for the main webapp process, so the new files were not shown without the cache.
Fixed a bug where the audit log for uploaded files would include only the outer path but not the uploaded filename.
Secured the /install route so only administrator can see it.
Fixed a bug with pirana file removal where the path was set to the cluster name instead of user name.

Raised the correct exception for cluster creation errors, which will now be shown to the user.
Changed the register page to not disable the button when the local linux user does not exist. It was not needed and caused the disabled state to stick when the modal was closed without clicking a button.

Changed regular text field metadata box to be called "TextBox"
Added support for DateField to non-html5 browsers using "Zebra-Datepicker"
Fixed a bug where an error would occur if a user logged out after their session had been expired for a while

Added second nmfe binary to list of wrapped binaries for auditing. This second nmfe is used by pirana.
Added auditing entries for adding and removing nodes.

Corrected audit for adding/removing nodes to convert objectID to string.
Added two additional executables to audit list: /usr/bin/runrecord /usr/bin/psn_clean
Fixed a bug where the correct amount of pages were not shown on the audit because integer divion was being done instead of floating point division.
Added a bunch of missing icons for jquery-ui (required for calender on audit page)
Added option for post commit URL which allows post-commit-hook to work with remote SVN repositories.
Sonic 2.1 release

Fixed a bug in the svnadmin javascript which did not clear the binding for adding a new selection to a 'select' metadata field, causing multiple blank fields to b e created in some cases.
Completely refactored some functions in the cluster create/delete/turn on/off whatever. The 'setup' hash table is no longer used, and arguments are not explicit. The 'prep' function for beginning to create a new cluster is also refactored to be generic, so it can be used for the new citrix clusters.

-Add Citrix Cluster functionality
-Changed internal function calling to use many arguments instead of one dictionary, which became confusing to remember
-Changed default functionality for compute cluster AMI behavior. The ini file will take precedence unless an override is specified in the users DB entry.
